Previous Next Putnam Investments to buy Toys "R" Us and Babies "R" Us Canada from Fairfax The Canadian Press 1 day ago VAUGHAN, Ont. — Putman Investments says it will purchase Toys "R" Us and Babies "R" Us Canada from affiliates of Fairfax Financial Holdings Limited The Ancaster, Ont.-based investment company did not reveal the value or terms of the deal. Toys "R" Us and Babies "R" Us Canada employs almost 5,000 people between its Vaughan, Ont. head office and 81 stores in 10 provinces. Family-owned Putman Investments is run by Doug Putman, who owns Sunrise Records and Entertainment Limited and purchased HMV in 2019.
